The '''Sichuan thrush''' or '''Sichuan forest thrush''' ('''''Zoothera griseiceps''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the [[Turdidae|thrush]] family. It breeds in central China and winters in northern Vietnam. The Sichuan thrush was formerly considered as conspecific with the [[alpine thrush]] and the [[Himalayan thrush]] as the '''plain-backed thrush''' until split in 2016.

